## 5. Git Workflow

### When Starting Task

```bash
# 1. Create branch
git checkout -b T##-short-name

# 2. Make changes
# ... write code ...

# 3. Commit frequently (not just at end)
git commit -m "T##: Add X feature

- Detail 1
- Detail 2"

# 4. Final commit
git commit -m "Complete T## - task name

- Main accomplishment 1
- Main accomplishment 2

Part of M# Milestone
Tests: ✅ passed
Issues: None
Risks: None"

# 5. Push
git push origin T##-short-name
```

### Commit Message Format

```
T##: Brief one-liner

- Detailed point 1
- Detailed point 2

Optional: Part of M# milestone
Optional: Tests: ✅/❌
Optional: Issues: #X
Optional: Risks: #X
```

