## 7. Testing Expectations

When implementing features:

1. **Unit Tests** (with each component)
   ```python
   async def test_create_user():
       service = UserService(mock_db)
       user = await service.create_user(123)
       assert user.id == 123
   ```

2. **Integration Tests** (when integrating components)
   ```python
   async def test_complete_subscription_flow():
       # Create user
       # Create subscription
       # Verify in DB
   ```

3. **E2E Tests** (for complete flows)
   ```python
   async def test_user_registers_and_buys():
       # User /start
       # User /buy
       # Verify subscription active
   ```

---

## 8. Code Quality Checklist

Before committing:

- [ ] Code follows PEP 8 (use `black` if available)
- [ ] Type hints on all functions
- [ ] Docstrings on all public functions
- [ ] Error handling complete
- [ ] No hardcoded values
- [ ] No global state
- [ ] Tests written (if applicable)
- [ ] No SQL injection risks
- [ ] Async/await used correctly
- [ ] Logging added for debugging
- [ ] No unused imports
- [ ] No print() statements
- [ ] No commented-out code

